article.description: Zach Copeland scored 15 points and Illinois State beat Division-II Lindenwood University 79-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Illinois State beats Div. II Lindenwood University 79-62
article.linkText: Illinois State beats Div. II Lindenwood University 79-62
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- Zach Copeland scored 15 points and Illinois State beat Division-II Lindenwood University 79-62 on Saturday. Copeland was 6 of 9 from the field including three from distance for the Redbirds (4-2). Josh Jefferson added 14 points and Phil Fayne had 13 points and seven boards. Illinois State shot 54 percent from the field compared to 35 percent for Lindenwood and had a 39-33 rebounding edge. Copeland drained two 3-pointers and Jefferson hit another as part of a 17-8 start for the Redbirds and they led all the way to a 36-22 advantage at the break. Illinois State extended its lead to 49-27 on a hail of 3-pointers by William Tinsley and Milik Yarbrough early in the second half and to 55-30 on another Tinsley 3 before Lindenwood had a chance to close to 67-53 with 4:01 left. Chris King scored 14 points for the Lions. Chandler Diekvoss led with nine rebounds in addition to his 11 points.
